
[1]abbreviate

   ABBRE'VIATE, v.t. [from Latin abbrevio, brevio, from brevis, short]

   1. To shorten; to make shorter by contracting the parts. [In this
   sense, not much used, nor often applied to material substances.]

   2. To shorten; to abridge by the omission or defalcation of a part; to
   reduce to a smaller compass; as to abbreviate a writing.

   3. In mathematics, to reduce fractions to the lowest terms.
